cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper presents a framework for studying adversarial attacks on discrete data, specifically text classification models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed methods on various state-of-the-art models, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
